This is a limited case of "loop unswitching".  Please consider a more general solution, where
```
for (i = 0..N) {
  // statement A
  if (invariant-condition) {
    // statement B
  } else {
    // statement C
  }
  // statement D
}
```
is transformed into
```
if (invariant-condition) {
  for (i = 0..N) {
    // statement A
    // statement B
    // statement D
  }
} else {
  for (i = 0..N) {
    // statement A
    // statement C
    // statement D
  }
}
```

Using the same logic you could unswitch attribute statements, if needed.

